The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 London (PTI): An Indian student and five others are suing a US-based research firm for a botched drug trial here for which they had volunteered only to be admitted to intensive care with multiple organ failures. 

 Nav Modi, 24, and the five are claiming millions of pounds in damages caused by the trial conducted by Paraxel in May. Their heads swelled like balloons and organs failed after being given the experimental drug at a hospital in northwest London. 

 Dubai (PTI): The 18-month-old twin children of an Indian couple in Saudi Arabia are in dire straits as their parents have been detained by police in connection with the murder of their maid. Relatives said she had run away from Roy Joseph and Bijis house on July 7 with a bunch of keys and a cellphone. The couple were detained after she was found dead. 

 New Delhi (PTI): The Union home ministry has said the Central Industrial Security Force will take charge of the security of the highly vulnerable Delhi Metro rail. Currently, Delhi police are in charge of its overall security with the CISF assisting them.

 Ahmedabad (PTI): Thirty people have been arrested in connection with the attack on a police station in Surendranagar district of Gujarat. A mob, which wanted the police to hand over a youth who had allegedly raped a minor girl, had attacked the station.




